  "texts": [
    "Extending the success of LLM-based test generation to these domains presents a significant opportunity.",
    "For instance, in integration testing, LLMs can be utilized to understand and generate complex call sequences across multiple modules.",
    "At the system level, they can automatically generate end-to-end test scenarios based on user manuals or requirement documents.",
    "In non-functional testing, LLMs can assist in generating realistic workload profiles for performance testing or identifying hazardous inputs that may expose security vulnerabilities.",
    "Specifically, existing research has explored leveraging LLMs to automatically generate 'witness tests' (tests that fail before a fix and pass after it) for known security vulnerabilities."
  ],
